OL,3,CWhere are the wildfires and how
OL,4,Cdangerous are they?
OL,6,FWildfire risk is linked to weather.
OL,7,FHigh temperatures, low rainfall, dry
OL,8,Fvegetation, low humidity, and strong
OL,9,Fwinds can all increase the chance of
OL,10,Ffires starting and spreading.
OL,12,FThe Met Office's Fire Severity Index
OL,13,F(FSI) helps identify when weather
OL,14,Fconditions could lead to more severe
OL,15,Fwildfires.
OL,17,FCombined with information from Natural
OL,18,FEngland, the government adviser for
OL,19,FEngland's environment, it helps
OL,20,Fhighlight areas where wildfire risk
OL,21,Fmay be higher.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
